def fibonacci(n, memo=None):
    if memo is None:
        memo = {}
    if n in memo:
        return memo[n]

    if n <= 1:
        memo[n] = n
    else:
        memo[n] = fibonacci(n - 1, memo) + fibonacci(n - 2, memo)

    return memo[n]
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Explanation:
• The function uses a dictionary named memo to store values of already computed Fibonacci numbers.
• If n is already in memo, return its value directly to save computation time.
• If n ≤ 1, the Fibonacci number is just n (0 or 1).
• Otherwise, recursively calculate fibonacci(n-1) and fibonacci(n-2), store in memo, and return the sum.
